<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bonds Hits Historic Home Run  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Barry Bonds hit career home run No. 476 in
the fourth inning of San Francisco's game against San Diego on
Wednesday night, moving into sole possession of 18th place on the
all-time list.
</P>
<P>
   For Bonds, who was tied with Stan Musial and Willie Stargell
before connecting against Brian Meadows, it was also his 300th home
run for the Giants.
</P>
<P>
   The homer, a three-run shot that tied the game at 3, landed in
McCovey Cove, the water just outside the right-field fence at
Pacific Bell Park.
</P>
<P>
   It was the fifth ''splash hit'' for Bonds this season, and was
only the sixth time a ball has landed into the water on the fly.
Dodgers catcher Todd Hundley is the only opponent to reach McCovey
Cove.
</P>
</TEXT>
