<HEADLINE> Cards Outfielder Lankford Returns  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX (AP) -- Ray Lankford rejoined the St. Louis Cardinals'
lineup Wednesday after taking three days off following the shooting
death of his brother.
</P>
<P>
   Percival Thomley, 19, of Inglewood, Calif., was killed Saturday
night while visiting a friend and died Sunday at Los Angeles County
Harbor-UCLA Medical Center.
</P>
<P>
   Lankford left the Cardinals the same day, skipping the
Cardinals' game at Minnesota.
</P>
<P>
   Inglewood homicide detective Mark Campbell identified Thomley as
Lankford's brother and said Lankford, a Los Angeles native, spent
the time with his mother.
</P>
<P>
   The Cardinals made his 60th start of the season in left field in
the game Wednesday night against the Arizona Diamondbacks.
</P>
</TEXT>
