<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Larry Walker Ejected From Game  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Colorado Rockies outfielder Larry Walker was
ejected from Wednesday night's game at Los Angeles by plate umpire
Scott Higgins after arguing a called third strike to end the sixth
inning.
</P>
<P>
   Walker, whose first-inning single was the only hit allowed by
Dodgers right-hander Kevin Brown through six innings, briefly
protested after Higgins called him out on a full-count pitch and
was tossed.
</P>
<P>
   Butch Huskey, acquired from Minnesota over the weekend, replaced
Walker in left field.
</P>
<P>
   The game was tied 1-1 when Walker, who entered the game hitting
.324, was ejected, but the Dodgers took a 4-1 lead in the bottom of
the sixth on Dave Hansen's three-run homer.
</P>
</TEXT>
