<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liberty 78, Storm 55  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE (AP) -- Vickie Johnson scored 18 points to lead the New
York Liberty to a 78-55 victory over the Seattle Storm on Wednesday
night.
</P>
<P>
   It was the first and only meeting between the teams going in
opposite directions. New York (13-9) has won a season-high six
straight games while the Storm (3-19) have lost six in a row.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson finished 6-of-11 from the field in the game, but was
4-of-5 in the second half when the Liberty pulled away for their
largest margin of victory this season.
</P>
<P>
   Tari Phillips had 17 points and nine rebounds for the Liberty,
while Becky Hammon added 16 points.
</P>
<P>
   Kamila Vodichkova and Quacy Barnes each scored 12 points to pace
Seattle.
</P>
<P>
   Seattle's Edna Campbell returned after missing 10 games with a
sprained right ankle. Campbell, the team's leading scorer at 15.5
points, finished with two points on 1-of-9 shooting in 26 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Hammon was responsible for New York's quick start. She scored 13
points in the first half on 5-of-6 shooting, including all three
attempts from outside the 3-point line.
</P>
<P>
   Hammon's second 3-pointer gave New York a 14-3 lead just 4:37
into the game.
</P>
<P>
   Seattle struggled on offense early, scoring only six points over
the opening 5:24, all by Sonja Henning.
</P>
<P>
   The Liberty closed the first half with an 8-0 run to take a
42-29 lead.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
