<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 49ers Schulters Misses Practice  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   STOCKTON, Calif. (AP) -- Pro Bowl safety Lance Schulters was
missing from the San Francisco 49ers' first day of practice,
apparently staging a bizarre holdout.
</P>
<P>
   ''His wife put him on the plane, but somewhere along the way he
took a detour,'' said John McVay, 49ers' director of football
operations.
</P>
<P>
   Team officials hadn't talked to Schulters as of Wednesday
afternoon, but they believe he dumped established agent Alan
Herman, and hired another representative who is telling him not to
report. Still, nobody is quite sure what happened.
</P>
<P>
   ''We've been told it could be a contract thing,'' coach Steve
Mariucci said.
</P>
<P>
   Schulters is in the final season of a three-year deal for
$358,000. Preliminary talks of a contract extension have been held,
but team officials said it didn't seem to be a priority for the
team.
</P>
<P>
   ''I talked to Lance on Thursday,'' defensive coordinator Jim
Mora said. ''He didn't mention anything about it. He said, 'I'll
see you on the 18th.' This just doesn't sound like Lance.''
</P>
<P>
   Herman was unavailable for comment Wednesday, but his office
said he would probably issue a statement Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The 49ers signed tackle Scott Gragg, defensive end Anthony
Pleasant and wide receiver/kick returner Kevin Williams. Gragg was
a four-year starter with the New York Giants but became a salary
cap victim in the offseason.
</P>
<P>
   ''I wanted to come here,'' Gragg said. ''I told my agent to keep
answering the phone, but to always keep an eye on the 49ers.''
</P>
<P>
   Gragg provides insurance in case left tackle Dave Fiore
struggles with his rehabilitation from knee surgery. Fiore is
healing ahead of schedule, but the 49ers are wary as he has
undergone five knee operations in his five years in the league.
</P>
<P>
   Pleasant is angling for a starting position at defensive end,
something he has done for the bulk of his 10-year career.
</P>
<P>
   Williams played with the Dallas Cowboys and won two Super Bowls
before signing as a free agent with Arizona. He spent the last two
years in Buffalo, and fills the 49ers need for a punt returner.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-07-20-00 0045 </TRAILER>
