<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ex-Albion guard fined on sex charge  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ALBION, N.Y. (AP) - A former prison guard was sentenced to three
years probation and fined $1,000 on charges related to his having
had sex with a female inmate.
</P>
<P>
   Robert Kozak, who worked at the Albion Correctional Facility,
pleaded guilty last month to official misconduct. He was originally
charged with third-degree rape.
</P>
<P>
   Kozak admitted to having a relationship with the woman that
ended in March. The woman said the relationship was consensual, but
according to state law an inmate is incapable of consenting to such
a relationship.
</P>
<P>
   The two first got together in the woman's cubicle, then in the
correction officers' bathroom, court papers show.
</P>
<P>
   Kozak was not allowed to remain a corrections officer because of
his conviction on the misdemeanor charge.
</P>
<P>
   The inmate's lawyer, Arthur Golbart of New York City, said he
wanted Kozak tested for HIV because he said Kozak had been accused
of previous sexual relationships with female inmates.
</P>
<P>
   Kozak is the second Albion guard to lose his job in the last
year following allegations sex with inmates. Another guard was
convicted of sexual abuse in September.
</P>
<P>
   Albion Correctional Facility is about 30 miles west of Rochester
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
