<HEADLINE> 8 Killed in Egpyt Builing Collapse  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CAIRO, Egypt (AP) -- At least eight people were killed and 17
others injured when a clothing factory gutted by fire collapsed in
the Mediterranean city of Alexandria, police said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The dead included five firefighters and the commander of
Alexandria's Fire Brigade.
</P>
<P>
   They were inside the factory investigating the cause of a fire
that broke out late Wednesday when the building suddenly collapsed,
officials said.
</P>
<P>
   The cause of the fire in the poor Izbat Saad suburb of this port
city had not been determined.
</P>
