<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-20 12:32 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 131; Nasdaq Adds 104  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks surged higher Thursday as investors
poured back into the markets seeking bargains after two days of
losses.
</P>
<P>
   In midday trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial
average was up 130.82 at 10,826.90.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor's
500 index was up 12.91 at 1,494.87, and the Nasdaq composite index
was up 103.59 at 4,159.22.
</P>
<P>
   The markets also took comfort from comments by Federal Reserve
Board Chairman Alan Greenspan, who said in testimony before a
Senate committee that the economy is showing signs of slowing.
</P>
<P>
   However, investors shrugged off indications by Greenspan that
the Fed is still concerned with the specter of rising inflation.
</P>
<P>
   Technology stocks were up across the board, led by fiber-optics
company SDL Inc., up $49 to $408.625. The company is being acquired
by parts maker JDS Uniphase.
</P>
<P>
   JDS Uniphase shares also soared, rising $16.75 to $123.50, on
news the company is being added to the benchmark S&AMP;P 500 index.
</P>
<P>
   Computer maker IBM reported better-than-expected earnings after
the market closed Wednesday. Investors flocked to the stock,
pushing it up $9.782 to $113.938.
</P>
<P>
   IBM's earnings was apparently the catalyst for the shift in
momentum because Wednesday's selloff, which saw the Nasdaq Stock
Market lose 122 points and the Dow Jones industrial average fall 44
points, was spurred by disappointed investors who sold the shares
of tech companies that didn't live up to high earnings
expectations.
</P>
<P>
   Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 3-to-2 margin on the
New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 499.01 million
shares, well ahead of Wednesday's pace.
</P>
<P>
   The Russell 2000 index was up 5.30 at 533.16.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   New York Stock Exchange: http://www.nyse.com
</P>
<P>
   Nasdaq Stock Market: http://www.nasdaq.com
</P>
</TEXT>
