<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Martha Stewart Story  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHARLESTON, S.C. (AP) -- The Associated Press reported
erroneously on July 19 that Martha Stewart personally apologized to
a Charleston handbag designer for changes to one of the designer's
bags in a photo display in Martha Stewart Weddings magazine.
</P>
<P>
   The apology and offer of a retraction to Mary Norton came from
the magazine, said Samantha Schabel of the Susan Magrino Agency, a
spokeswoman for the publication. Stewart is chairwoman and chief
executive of Martha Stewart Living Omnimedia Inc., which owns the
magazine.
</P>
<P>
   The story also misspelled Magrino's last name as Magrin.
</P>
