<HEADLINE> Winona Ryder: I'm really a blonde  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - Winona Ryder is turning a Hollywood hair
tradition upside-down.
</P>
<P>
   The dark-haired Generation X movie star admits she's really a
blonde.
</P>
<P>
   Ryder tells Harper's Bazaar magazine she started dying her blond
hair blue and purple when she was 11 or 12.
</P>
<P>
   ''When I auditioned for (the movie) Lucas, my hair was black and
they wanted to keep it,'' she said in an interview for the issue
that came out Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Ryder appears in the forthcoming movie ''Autumn in New York''
opposite Richard Gere.
</P>
