<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that were moving substantially or trading
heavily Thursday on the New York Stock Exchange and the Nasdaq
Stock Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
   IBM, up $12.907 to $117.063
</P>
<P>
   The computer maker reported earnings from continuing operations
rose 14 percent in the second-quarter, beating analysts'
expectations. But net income and revenue dropped slightly from the
year-ago period. While personal computer and disk drive sales were
disappointing, IBM officials attributed the strong earnings to
growth in Web server sales and the sale of so-called middleware
software used in e-business, especially Web management and database
programs.
</P>
<P>
   Lucent Technologies Inc., down $10.5 to $54.125
</P>
<P>
   The phone-equipment maker warned investors that profits for the
next two quarters will be lower then previously expected. Lucent
also said it had a fiscal third-quarter loss from operations of 9
cents a share, compared with a profit of 24 cents in the year-ago
quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Boeing, down 18.8 cents to $46.063
</P>
<P>
   The airplane maker's stock was upgraded to buy from market
perform by an analyst at Donaldson Lufkin &AMP; Jenrette. On Wednesday,
the company reported second-quarter operating earnings of 75 cents
a share, above analysts estimates of 67 cents a share.
</P>
<P>
   Wal-Mart Stores, $60, unchanged from yesterday
</P>
<P>
   Wal-Mart is planning a major expansion in Germany, adding 50
stores to the 95 it already operates there.
</P>
<P>
NASDAQ
</P>
<P>
   JDS Uniphase Corp., up $21.375 to $128.125
</P>
<P>
   The fiber-optic parts maker replaced Rite Aid Corp. in the
benchmark Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 Index after the close of trading
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   Extreme Networks Inc., up $32.25 to $148.25
</P>
<P>
   The maker of computer-networking equipment announced it will
split its stock 2-for-1.
</P>
<P>
   Check Point Software Technologies Ltd., up $18.375 to $243.25
</P>
<P>
   The maker of corporate software for blocking hacker attacks
reported second-quarter earnings of 50 cents a share, well above
Wall Street analysts' estimates of 42 cents.
</P>
<P>
   Conexant Systems Inc., down $9.875 to $39.063
</P>
<P>
   The computer chip maker for communications equipment announced
plans to buy two closely held companies, NetPlane Systems and
Novanet Semiconductor, for $285 million. In addition, Conexant said
fiscal third-quarter chips sales for cellular phones were stagnant
compared to the prior quarter because of a sales slowdown in South
Korea.
</P>
</TEXT>
