<HEADLINE> HUD Judge Awards $1M to Advocate  </HEADLINE>
By CLAUDE R. MARX
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- A federal judge on Thursday awarded a former
fair housing advocate $1.1 million in damages from a neo-Nazi group
that displayed intimidating images of her on its Web site.
</P>
<P>
   Administrative Law Judge Alan Heifetz ruled that white
supremacist Ryan Wilson's neo-Nazi ALPHA HQ group had tried to
intimidate Bonnie Jouhari into not fighting housing discrimination.
Heifetz works for the U.S. Department of Housing and Urban
Development, which filed the suit on behalf of Jouhari against
ALPHA HQ.
</P>
<P>
   Jouhari, who is white, worked for the Reading-Berks Human
Relations Council in Reading, Pa. and helped victims of housing
discrimination file complaints.
</P>
<P>
   The decision, which can be appealed to another HUD official and
then to the U.S. Court of Appeals, awards damages for emotional
distress to Jouhari and her daughter. It also reimburses both women
for lost salary, moving expenses and the cost of therapy. Wilson
and his organization must also pay $33,000 in civil penalties.
</P>
<P>
   ''If dedicated and talented fair housing advocates can be
targeted, intimidated and harassed with impunity then the
enforcement mechanism of that (Fair Housing) Act will be rendered
impotent,'' Heifetz wrote in his decision.
</P>
<P>
   Jouhari said she felt so intimidated that she moved out of the
state with her daughter, Danielle Horton, who is biracial.
</P>
<P>
   ''I hope today's decision serves as a deterrent to anyone else
who thinks they can get away with such torture,'' Jouhari said in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
   Wilson could not be reached for comment.
</P>
<P>
   In May, a former Pennsylvania Ku Klux Klan leader agreed to pay
Jouhari and Horton 10 percent of his annual income for a decade and
apologize to them on his cable television program to settle a
federal discrimination lawsuit.
</P>
<P>
   Roy E. Frankhouser admitted that during his ''White Forum''
cable show, which airs in Reading, he displayed ''hateful'' images
of Jouhari from the ALPHA HQ Web site. One animated picture showed
Jouhari's office being blown up.
</P>
</TEXT>
