<HEADLINE> Logger dies after being struck by tree  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   BLEECKER, N.Y. (AP) - A 31-year-old man was killed when a
falling tree hit him in the head, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Richard W. Boice was logging in a rugged area of Hogback
Mountain in Fulton County about 10:30 a.m. Tuesday when he was
struck in the head by a falling tree, the Fulton County Sheriff's
Department said.
</P>
<P>
   Rescuers negotiated wet and rough terrain to reach Boice then
carried him out three-quarters of a mile to a waiting state police
helicopter. He died at Albany Medical Center Hospital of massive
head trauma.
</P>
<P>
   Bleecker is 43 miles northwest of Albany.
</P>
