<DOCNO> APW20000720.0210 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-20 22:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Valderrama Top-Vote Getter for MLS  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Tampa Bay midfielder Carlos Valderrama, Los
Angeles midfielder Mauricio Cienfuegos and Galaxy forward Cobi
Jones became five-time MLS All-Stars when they were elected
Thursday to start in the July 29 game in Columbus, Ohio.
</P>
<P>
   Valderrama, a former star for Colombia's national team and Major
League Soccer's assists leader with 19, received the most votes,
57,319.
</P>
<P>
   German star Lothar Matthaeus, who played poorly for the New
York/New Jersey MetroStars before leaving for the European
Championship and has appeared in only one MLS game since, was
elected to start at defender for the East.
</P>
<P>
   Jones and Chicago's Ante Razov, who scored the U.S. goal in
Sunday's World Cup qualifier at Guatemala, were elected to start at
forward for the West, with Cienfuegos joined in the midfield by
Chicago's Chris Armas and Peter Nowak, Kansas City's Preki
Radosavljevic and San Jose's Khodadad Azizi.
</P>
<P>
   Robin Fraser and Greg Vanney of Los Angeles and Marcelo Balboa
of Colorado were elected to start at defender, and Kansas City's
Tony Meola -- the U.S. starter in the 1990 and 1994 World Cups, was
elected at goalkeeper.
</P>
<P>
   Adolfo Valencia of the MetroStars, another former Colombia
national team star, was elected to start at forward for the East
along with D.C. United's Jaime Moreno, a starter for Bolivia's
national team.
</P>
<P>
   Joining Valderrama and United's Marco Etcheverry -- another
Bolivian starter -- at midfield were the MetroStars' Clint Mathis
and Mark Chung, and Tampa Bay's Steve Ralston.
</P>
<P>
   Matthaeus is joined at defender by DC United's Eddie Pope and
Jeff Agoos, both starters for the U.S. national team.
</P>
<P>
   Mike Ammann of the MetroStars was elected at goalkeeper.
</P>
<P>
   Agoos, Etcheverry and Radosavljevic also were elected to their
fifth MLS All-Star games.
</P>
<P>
   Seven starters will be making their first All-Star appearance:
Ammann, Azizi, Mathis, Matthaeus, Razov, Valencia and Vanney.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
