<HEADLINE> House Votes To Lift Cuban Limits  </HEADLINE>
By ALAN FRAM
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- The House voted Thursday to lift limits
against U.S. food and drug sales to Cuba and against Americans
seeking to travel there in a major victory for farm, business and
other groups trying to ease the four-decade-old restrictions.
</P>
<P>
   With supporters arguing that increased contacts would help
weaken Fidel Castro's hold over the communist nation, the House
voted 232-186 to stop enforcing rules that limit the ability of
Americans to travel to Cuba.
</P>
<P>
   It then voted 301-116 to also halt enforcement of rules banning
U.S. exports there of food, and of rules limiting sales there of
American medicine.
</P>
</TEXT>
