<HEADLINE> URGENT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   EAST HAVEN, Conn. (AP) - An elderly man shot his estranged wife
then turned the gun on himself Thursday night in front of a crowd
that had gathered for a concert on the town's green, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The shooting occurred at about 9 p.m. in front of about 100 to
200 people, said Police Chief Leonard Gallo.
</P>
<P>
   The woman was seated in a lawn chair when the man walked up
behind her and fired one shot into the back of her head, police
said. He then walked a short distance away and shot himself in the
head, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The shooter, who appeared to be in his 70s, died at the scene,
Gallo said. His victim was in critical condition at a local
hospital, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Their identities had not been released Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
   ''It sounded like fireworks,'' said Phil Carrano, who was
attending the concert. ''Within ten seconds, not even, everyone
started to scatter. People took out their cell phones, and that's
when we knew they were shots, they were not fireworks.''
</P>
<P>
   Mayor Joseph Maturo called the shooting ''devastating''
</P>
<P>
   ''We do have stress management to help the witnesses,'' he said.
''This was supposed to be a fun night. This was supposed to be a
nice night.''
</P>
</TEXT>
